  "description": "Hydrothermal vent activity — Noise src1 carries the mineral turbulence, LoFiSaw src2 provides the industrial register, FM (fmDepth=0.38) adds the metallic harmonic distortion of superheated minerals. proc1=BP filter (650 Hz, reso=0.58) sculpts the vent roar; proc2=LP (1200 Hz) attenuates the harsh highs. This is the most aggressive Submerged preset by design: aggression=0.35, still well below Flux territory but energized by the thermal field. Journey Mode lets the vent evolve its chemistry. Four mods bring the vent to life: LFO->FilterCutoff shimmers, Env->FXMix surges, Velocity->Volume strikes like pressure release, Aftertouch->FilterReso tightens the jet.",
